        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Ring-Fenced Procedure \u2013 Group Consultations / MSBPO-19004 / 1.0"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Page  of"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "Historically each individual Trust will have redeployment processes in place for staff who are displaced as a result of change or for other substantial reasons e.g. ill health. There is currently no formal process across the Group for holding vacancies to support redeployment processes."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "As we continue to move forward with the Group Corporate Consultation processes at all bands, it is important that we acknowledge that some colleagues may be at risk as a result of these processes and it is important to have a Group wide approach to managing the vacancies across all three organisations during this time."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "In line with our legal obligations to mitigate redundancies, we are therefore setting out a proposal to be implemented with immediate effect to support the Corporate Consultation processes."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Definitions"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 5,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "TERM"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "DEFINITION"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "VCG"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Vacancy Control Group"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "HR"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Human Resources"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "OD"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Organisational Development"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "AfC"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Agenda For Change"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Roles and Responsibilities"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "Role and Responsibilities - Committees  Duties Are:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Executive Group should ensure the implementation of this procedure across the group and that all staff are treated fairly and equitably."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "Role and Responsibilities of Individuals within the Trust  Duties Are:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Role 1: Group Director Workforce of OD and Workforce Transformation is"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "responsible for the oversight of the generation and implementation of policies"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "and procedures relating to workforce matters;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Role : Group Associate Director of Resourcing are to ensure the publication and review of this procedure;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Role 3: Managers across group \u2013 To ensure that this procedure is adhered to and that all staff within their remit are aware of this procedure."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Proposal"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Clinical and non-clinical administration vacancies at all AFC bands across all sites, regardless of whether a site or group role, are ring-fenced for those staff who are displaced by an organisational change process, except for under the criteria set out in this paper."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "Details of these vacancies will be collated at the relevant site/group Vacancy Control Group (VCG) and forwarded to the site Associate Director of HR or their nominated representative."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "Each vacancy will be reviewed at the point in which it is received to establish whether there are any individuals suitable for consideration. If at this point there are no suitable redeployees then the role should be released. It is anticipated that this process may take up to seven working days."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "All posts are to be held back, and open only to redeployed staff, until the core programme of corporate reconfiguration is concluded, which is likely to be by September 2019. However, there are specific criteria based exceptions to this position:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Specific functions and teams that are business critical will have all roles exempted from this process. These teams must be agreed in advance (see point 6 for the panel who will make this judgement call). Examples of such teams for consideration would include:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Posts that are specifically essential to delivery of mandatory requirements for regulators, or contractually, will be considered exempt by agreement with the oversight panel;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Posts that require a specific skill set or technical knowledge, the absence of which will render a candidate unsuitable for consideration. Examples of this may include: cost accountants, procurement specialists, technical support and employee relations specialists;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where non-recruitment will result in patient harm, agreement to recruit may be given;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where it is evidenced that the group will be financially disadvantaged by not recruiting, then the post can be exempted from this process."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.5,
                "text": "If the hiring manager can demonstrate that delaying the advertisement of an open position to the end of the corporate configuration would cause unacceptable strain on the existing team or adversely affect the service provided, the position may be advertised in advance of this time. However unless it is a post requiring specialised skills as above, it should be ring fenced in the first instance for candidates at risk of redundancy. In that instance, it should be made available to people in the"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "redeployment pool for a period of seven days; after which it may be released for further recruitment if not already filled."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.6,
                "text": "It should not be considered a post has been agreed to go out to recruitment until there is formal confirmation from the oversight panel."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Exemption Process"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "The site Associate Director of HR or nominated representative should liaise with the appointing Manager and site Managing Director with regard to the critical nature of the job role. If it is viewed that the role is critical, in line with criteria above, and cannot be held, the site will need to provide a rationale for this view."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.2,
                "text": "Final agreement should be with the site Managing Director, Lead responsible Executive Director and Chief People and OD Director. These senior individuals may delegate to their Group Director level colleagues."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.3,
                "text": "If necessary, where there is a dispute on whether a post should be held the Deputy CEO will be asked to review and provide an organisational decision."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.4,
                "text": "The Recruitment team in partnership with HR Business Partners and the Change Team will oversee this process;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.5,
                "text": "Priority will be given to those staff on the redeployment register who are at risk of employment / redundancy above any other individual on the redeployment register;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.6,
                "text": "Opportunities will be placed on TRAC (recruitment system) for all staff who are on the redeployment register to access and they must express an interest in the roles that they wish to apply for."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.7,
                "text": "Where a vacancy has identified a match with the redeployment pool, the staff member will be entitled to a minimum trial period of one month. If this does not result in successful outcome the vacancy will be returned to the ring-fenced pool."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 57
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Legal Advice"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 58
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "Legal advice was sought in relation to the ring fencing of vacancies during a change programme, and the advice is that a review process should be in place to consider roles on an individual basis to ensure that there are individuals suitable for the opportunity."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 59
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 8.0,
                "text": "Consultation"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 60
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.1,
                "text": "Once this process has been agreed by the Executive team, communication will be provided to the recognised Trade Unions regarding the process, in line with our legal duty to mitigate redundancies as a result of the change programme."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 61
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 9.0,
                "text": "Review and Monitoring"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 62
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 9.1,
                "text": "This process will be reviewed in September 2019, remaining in place during the Corporate Consultation process, with further review should consultation processes conclude at a later point."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
